Level 1.01 is a sub-level located between [[Level 1]] and [[Level 2]] and is the first sub-level of [[Level 1]].

== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=1.01-2.jpg|caption=The entrance to Level 1.01}}'''Level 1.01''' is an infinite basement below [[Level 1]]. Entrances to the sub-level are rather difficult to encounter, as only a few are confirmed to exist by the [[M.E.G.]] '''Level 1.01''' consists of mostly empty basement/bunker corridors; these corridors are usually filled with dust and rare [[Object 1|Almond Water]] puddles. However, the water is not safe to drink due to the environment of the sub-level. Lying on the floor, there are small items that are covered in dust, and usually they are broken and unusable. These items include, but are not limited to: pens without any ink, broken pencils, empty batteries, rusty pipes, soggy sheets of cardboard, broken wires, and other small items. Small rusty pipes can be found sticking out of the walls; these pipes don't transport anything and are most of the time dysfunctional. Other than long, claustrophobic halls on this level, it is possible to find rare rooms that are connected to these hallways via a large, rusty bunker door. The door is rusty and is usually painted either green, yellow, or left unpainted. The doors are, however, most of the time open, so it is easy to access these rooms, although some of the doors are locked and are difficult to open. 

The aforementioned rooms are usually small, bunker-like, or basement rooms with various objects and furniture inside them. Most of the rooms are either boiler rooms, food storage rooms, or empty rooms. Boiler rooms are the most common on this level, featuring various boiler equipment that is rusty and broken down. Most of the equipment is barely functional when connected outside of the sub-level. Even if the boilers were fully functional, they would still be pointless, as the pipelines are severely damaged and cannot be repaired without breaking down the walls of the sub-level. Food storage is the second most common room type on this sub-level. It is one of the emptiest, as there are only shelves with broken glass on the floor,  while rotten vegetables are inside of glass jars and are most of the time either pickles or tomatoes; other rotten food may be present, such as garlic, onions, various mushrooms, etc. Empty rooms are the last type of rooms, and they are empty and have almost nothing inside them. Most of the time, inside these rooms, there are puddles of almond water, though these are often unsafe to drink.

{{Blurimage|file=1.01-3.jpg|caption=Empty room with working lights|align=left}}The level is mostly dark, as light bulbs are rare on the level only appearing on the ceiling of rooms, majority of light bulbs on the level are shattered, those that are not broken are most likely turned off since there is barely any power on the sub-level, or the wires connecting the light bulb to the central electricity system are presumably damaged. Those light bulbs that are working are emitting white light that is barely able to light up the room. Due to this, it is recommended to bring a flashlight or another object that can serve as a source of light while exploring the level. '''Level 1.01''' has a ventilation system, much like other systems on the level; it is mainly broken down, with damage having been done to the ducts. Most of the vents are filled with polluted Almond Water and various mold colonies. Do not approach the vents without proper protection, as mold colonies emit spores that are deadly to humans. Puddles of almond water are common near the ventilation system and are strictly prohibited from drinking. The vents generally only appear inside the basement hallways, so the bunker rooms are considered safe. 


'''Level 1.01'''<nowiki/>'s '''main danger''' for unprepared wanderers is the infestation with mold and moss colonies, which reside inside the ventilation system. They are, as stated above, deadly to humans due to the spores emitted by them. Moss colonies are considered safe, and they don't cause any harm aside from blocking the vents. Mold colonies, on the other hand, are dangerous and should not be approached. The mold at this level is capable of emitting spores into the air; these spores, when inhaled, can stack up inside the nose and throat, which will most likely lead to suffocation. After about an hour, the suffocated person will wake up, but they will become hostile towards any living thing they encounter, this includes humans and [[Entity List|Entities]]. See more about "Molded" below. Spores are also capable of stacking up in the almond water puddles found near the ventilation system. While the polluted almond water won't kill you, it is not recommended to drink the almond water found on this level. Due to the dangerous effects of spores, it is required to wear at least a gas mask for safe exploration.

{{Blurimage|file=0.01-1.jpg|caption=A hallway near the entrance}}'''Level 1.01''' is one of the warmest sub-layers of Level 1, with temperature being constant at 23 °C, which should be enough for water to evaporate slowly; however, the almond water puddles never evaporate on this level. It is currently presumed that the water is not entirely affected by temperature, as it is always cool compared to the general environment of the sub-level. While inside the sub-level, you can sometimes hear noises or people chatting that seem to be coming from above. These sounds are not a hallucination; they are actually coming from [[Level 1]] and can be somewhat heard. However, no matter how loudly a person may be on the sub-level, not a single sound will ever be heard on [[Level 1]]. The reason why this effect works in this manner is currently unknown. Rarely, basement hatches can be found on the floor of the sub-level. These hatches are located in both rooms and hallways, and they are always locked. It is presumed that the area below them is another basement or an extension of the sub-level. Currently, there are no known attempts to open the hatch, as below it could likely be an even more dangerous area/sub-level.

== Discovery ==

=== '''Pre / Early M.E.G''' ===
'''Level 1.01'''<nowiki/>'s first hatch was discovered shortly after the discovery of [[Level 1]]. At the time, there were only two known hatches, both of which were at the infinite warehouse segment of the level. Basement hatches were considered impossible to open, as there were no required tools at that time, and information about the backrooms as a whole was mostly based on various rumors and single eyewitness accounts. Locals have claimed to have heard scratching noises below the hatches, and thus, it was presumed that something dangerous was lurking below them, and these hatches should not be opened under any circumstances.

During the early days of M.E.G., the rumors about "something dangerous below [[Level 1]]" were still really popular, and there was no way of disproving them other than opening the hatch. Base First Light was established recently, and at that time, they were mostly clearing "colonies" of entities near the base. They cleared the area surrounding the hatch, making it a blockpost for wanderers to pass through and defend against entities. The hatch itself was never opened; there were attempts by some of the wanderers, but they were always stopped by [[M.E.G.]] operatives near them, as it was still considered to be dangerous. [[M.E.G.]] workers who were at the block-post had debunked the rumors about the scratching noises below the hatch.

=== '''Operation "Below 1"''' ===
On 10.01.2016 [DD/MM/YYYY], Base First Light began planning a series of experiments regarding the basement hatch, which involved determining whether the hatch is truly indestructible or merely anomalously tough. The hatch was presumed to be out of concrete. The planning of the operation concluded on 17 January 2016, with three steps outlined for its execution. These steps were:

* '''''1.'''''  Making sure all unauthorized personnel/wanderers are at least 500m away from the block post so that nobody can interfere with the operation and remove all risks of potential harm to wanderers / other M.E.G operatives

* '''''2.'''''  Gathering rope and several jack-hammers from various sources and testing which are the most effective. After testing, gather only the jackhammers that have done the most damage. If there are no signs of damage done to the hatch, abort the mission until further notice.

* ''3.'' After gathering all the resources needed, proceed with forcefully breaking the hatch under the supervision of armed personnel. Once opened, use the rope to climb down and snap a quick picture. After that, flee the area below immediately and report the results to Base First Light.

On 25.01.2016, the plan was fully approved by M.E.G., and Base First Light began receiving the resources needed for the operation. The area surrounding the block post was restricted on 29.01.2016, and the next day, the first tests started. Unfortunately, on 01.02.2016 [[Phenomenon 12|The Flicker]] event occurred in the whole backrooms, as a result, the operation was scrapped until further notice and the block post was abandoned. Eventually, on 26.04.2016, [[Level 1]] would regain power, marking the end of the blackout and return of the "normal" style of life

=== '''Post Flicker''' ===
After the events of the flicker, Operation "Below 1" was cancelled, as the level and Base First Light were undergoing major restoration and dealing with a migration crisis. Two years later, the block post that was near the hatch was reopened under the new code name "First line" with 3 M.E.G members being constantly present at all times. Shortly after the reopening of the block post, operation "Below 1" was being reconsidered since there were many rumors about what was below the hatch that were made during the flicker; the most popular of these was that below the hatch was a safe place, isolated from the rest of the backrooms with food or water. Eventually, after the operation had concluded, it was discovered that below [[Level 1]] there was a presumably infinite old basement.

== Entities ==
Currently, on the level, there are no officially confirmed entities, although unofficially, "The Molded" are considered to be a level-exclusive entity.

=== '''The Molded''' ===
The Molded are humanoid entities that are only present on '''Level 1.01''', these entities are hostile to any living thing that they hear, so it is advised to be quiet near them. The Molded are actually corpses that were suffocated by the spores emitted from mold colonies. Most of the time, these entities were researchers who went to the sublevel without protection and were suffocated. Most of the entities are not immune to the spores, and they can also be turned into The Molded, sharing some properties with human victims. All species of The Molded share three things in common:

* '''''1'''''.  All of The Molded have enhanced hearing; it is estimated that their hearing is at least twice as good as human hearing.
* '''''2'''''. Blood of the molded is always dark red with black dots, regardless of whether The Molded were an entity or a human before the suffocation. Research on the blood has concluded that the blood is infested with the spores.
*
* '''''3.''''' After the body has turned into The Molded, the corpse will lose its eyes via rotting away. Due to this, all species of The Molded are blind.

Currently, most, if not all, of The Molded are killed after they are researched; their status as a separate entity or an environmental hazard is still uncertain, and thus, they are currently unclassified.

== Outposts, Bases and Colonies ==
While no colonies exist within Level 1.01, the block post near the hatch acts as an "outpost" for the level.

=== M.E.G block post "First Line" ===

*Has 3–4 members present at all times
*Checks wanderers for any dangerous items before they enter Base First Light
*Currently blocks the entrance to '''Level 1.01''' to avoid any more casualties caused by the level's environment

== Entrances and Exits ==

=== Entrances ===

*Entering a Basement hatch on [[Level 1]] will lead you here; currently, this is the only way to enter this sub-level.

=== Exits ===

*Going back the way you came leads back to [[Level 1]].
*Going to the dead end of a corridor and turning around will reveal a wooden door; walking through that door will take you to a random [[Level 1]] sub-level.
